name: Legung Luwih (balinese lifestyle)
address: Jl. Legung No.Br, Tunjuk, Kec. Marga, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82221, Indonesia
review 1: We’ve had a blast! Thanks so much for the warm welcome and all the loving memories. We lost our European soul and we can’t thank you enough for that. We learned traditional dances, how to craft offerings, talked to the priest, prepared and had dinner for the family, hiked in the forest, planted rice in the rice fields and finished with offerings to the Gods during the praying ceremony. THANK YOU for making our honeymoon so much better.
review 2: The day was phenomenal. The friendliest and interesting family you can wish for with a day full of hands-on experience of all parts Bali culture, from religion to cooking to living, from how to cook to how to make rice, palm sugar to coconut oil. Included a school and market visit. It's something not to miss. Just go.
review 3: One organization running by small family overing you tour to traditional market, tour to local school, and the tradition how running life in daily in Bali such as coocing traditional Bali Food, make equipment for ceremony, proces make brown sugar, and activity covensional to grow padi plantation.
review 4: Very good experience, we were a group of 9 friends and we liked this moment in the Balinese family, it was the best way to discover their culture !!! They are very kind and we had tears in our eyes when we left !
review 5: what a beautiful day we spent !!!  this wonderful family received us in all simplicity, to teach us the customs and high points of their daily lives.  traditional market, where we took the time to choose, at the school of the village where we were received in song, a day full of activities, cooking, rice field, dance.  everything was perfect .  I recommend 100% this wonderful traditional Balinese day.  Thank you to the whole family for this warm welcome.
